{"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Checkbox is a UI element that allows to select multiple options from a set of mutually non exclusive choices."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Checkbox item covers a wider range of contexts by allowing to toggle the visibility of additional text labels and icon assets."}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/s16SendableMetatypeP","doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/7SwiftUI4ViewP"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","kind":"attribute","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSCheckboxItem"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"mentions","mentions":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/Controls"]},{"content":[{"anchor":"Layouts","level":2,"text":"Layouts","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The component can be rendered as two different layouts:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}]},{"type":"text","text":": the component has a leading indicator, a label and optional helper texts, and an optional trailing decorative icon"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"reversed"}]},{"type":"text","text":": like the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"default"}]},{"type":"text","text":" layout but with a trailing checkbox indicator and a leading optional image"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Indicator-states","text":"Indicator states","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The checkbox indicator has three available states:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"selected"}]},{"type":"text","text":": the checkbox is filled with a tick, the user has made the action to select the checkbox"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"unselected"}]},{"type":"text","text":": the checkbox is empty, does not contain a tick, the user has made the action to unselect or did not select yet the checkbox"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you are looking for a checkbox component with three states, use instead "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItemIndeterminate"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Particular cases","level":2,"anchor":"Particular-cases"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem","type":"reference"},{"text":" can be related to an error situation, for example troubles for a formular.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"A dedicated look and feel is implemented for that if the ","type":"text"},{"code":"isError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" flag is risen.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"In that case if the component displayed an icon, this icon will be replaced automatically by an error icon.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In addition, the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem"},{"type":"text","text":" can be in read only mode, i.e. the user cannot interact with the component yet but this component must not be considered"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as disabled."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The component does not follow the right-to-left (RTL) \/ left-to-right (LTR) mode returned by the system as it could have some meaning","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to have for example the indicator in trailing position for LTR mode and vice versa.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However, if the component has an icon in leading position (RTL mode) or in trailing position (LTR), the content of the icon is never changed.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It could lead to a loss of meaning or semantics in the icon. Thus a specific flag can be used to flip the icon content whatever the layout direction is.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It prevents the user do implement its own rules to flip or not image.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Rich-text","level":2,"text":"Rich text","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Rich text can only be used for error messages."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Strong text can be used sparingly to highlight key information within the content.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"No other text styles should be used.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Underlined text must not be applied manually (e.g. in error message), as it is commonly associated with hyperlinks and may mislead users.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Accessibility-considerations","level":2,"text":"Accessibility considerations","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Always check the results of rich text mode with high contrast, light and dark modes, and Voice Over vocalization."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Voice Over","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" will use several elements to describe the component: if component disabled \/ read only, if error context, the label and helper texts and a custom checkbox trait.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"No accessibility identifier is defined in OUDS side as this value remains in the users hands.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Forbidden-by-design","level":2,"text":"Forbidden by design","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a read only component.","type":"text"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both an error situation and a disabled component.","type":"text"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"The design system does not allow to have both a read only and a disabled component.","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Code-samples","text":"Code samples","type":"heading","level":2},{"syntax":"swift","code":["    \/\/ Supposing we have an unselected checkbox","    @Published var isOn: Bool = false","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"Hello world\", isOn: $isOn)","","    \/\/ Localizable from bundle can also be used","    OUDSCheckboxItem(LocalizedStringKey(\"agree_terms\"), bundle: Bundle.module, isOn: $isOn)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label, but in read only mode (user cannot interact yet, but not disabled).","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"Hello world\", isOn: $isOn, isReadOnly: true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label and a description as helper text.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"Bazinga!\", isOn: $isOn, description: \"Doll-Dagga Buzz-Buzz Ziggety-Zag\")","","    \/\/ A trailing checkbox with a label, a description and an icon.","    \/\/ The reversed layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"We live in a fabled world\",","                     isOn: $isOn,","                     description: \"Of dreaming boys and wide-eyed girls\",","                     isReversed: true,","                     icon: Image(decorative: \"ic_heart\"))","","    \/\/ If on error, add an error message can help user to understand error context","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"We live in a fabled world\",","                     isOn: $isOn,","                     isError: true,","                     errorText: \"Something wrong\",","                     hasDivider: true)","","    \/\/ A leading checkbox with a label, but disabled.","    \/\/ The default layout will be used here.","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"Hello world\", isOn: $isOn)","        .disabled(true)","","    \/\/ Never disable a read only or an error-related checkbox as it will crash","    \/\/ This is forbidden by design!","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"Hello world\", isOn: $isOn, isError: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"Hello world\", isOn: $isOn, isReadOnly: true).disabled(true) \/\/ fatal error"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you need to flip your icon depending to the layout direction or not (e.g. if RTL mode lose semantics  \/ meanings):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["    @Environment(\\.layoutDirection) var layoutDirection","","    OUDSCheckboxItem(\"Cocorico !\",","                     isOn: $selection,","                     icon: Image(systemName: \"figure.handball\"),","                     flipIcon: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft,","                     isInversed: layoutDirection == .rightToLeft)"]},{"type":"heading","text":"Suggestions","level":2,"anchor":"Suggestions"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"According to the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-checkbox","type":"reference"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the checkbox by default must be used in unselected state.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","level":2,"text":"Design documentation","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/r.orange.fr\/r\/S-ouds-doc-checkbox","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"unified-design-system.orange.com","type":"text"}],"overridingTitle":"unified-design-system.orange.com"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Themes-rendering","text":"Themes rendering","type":"heading","level":2},{"anchor":"Orange","level":3,"text":"Orange","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Orange"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Orange Compact","level":3,"anchor":"Orange-Compact"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_checkboxItem_OrangeCompact","type":"image"}]},{"anchor":"Sosh","level":3,"text":"Sosh","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Sosh"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","text":"Wireframe","level":3,"anchor":"Wireframe"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_checkboxItem_Wireframe","type":"image"}]},{"name":"Version","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"2.4.0 (Figma component design version)","type":"text"}]}],"style":"note","type":"aside"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Since","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0.12.0"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/oudscomponents\/oudscheckboxitem"]}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSComponents\/documentation\/OUDSComponents\/OUDSCheckboxItem\/init(_:isOn:description:icon:flipIcon:isReversed:isE